### â—The server **does not store** the JWT after sending it. Thatâ€™s the whole point of using JWTs.

> âœ… **JWTs are stateless.**
> Once the server creates and sends a JWT, **it forgets about it**. It doesnâ€™t store it in memory or in a database.

